The capacity for language is a characteristic of humans that has intrigued both philosophers and scientists and led to the creation of an academic discipline (linguistics). Using several examples describe how language skills (speech, grammar, semantics, p
rose, etc.) can influence the structure and functioning of the nervous system and reciprocally how the structure and functioning of the nervous system can affect the manifestation of language skills.
